title: Grateful Dead Live at Philadelphia Civic Center on 1984-04-21
description:
Set 1:
01. Crowd/Tuning
02. Alabama Getaway >
03. Promised Land
04. Friend Of The Devil
05. Me & My Uncle >
06. Mexicali Blues
07. West L.A. Fadeaway (tape change after song)
08. New Minglewood Blues
09. Tennessee Jed
10. Looks Like Rain
11. Deal

Disc 2

Set 2:
01. Crowd/tuning (left drop out)
02. Help On The Way > (left drop out at very beginning)
03. Slipknot
04. Franklin's Tower
05. Playing In The Band
06. China Doll
07. I Don't Need Love (tape change at beginngin - bearly noticable)
08. Drums
09. Space
10. Wharf Rat
11. Throwing Stones// changes to LMA source.
12. Not Fade Away

Encore
13. Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: - Pretty good job for an off night, dude. Tape not overly cloudy, very well EQ balanced. Show starts off pretty solid, first set stays steady but unremarkable. Second set is lackluster, and Brent's new song, once interesting, is now trite and intrusive. All in all, not a great show.
